The paper deals with the problem of sampling a random signal with sparse support in frequency domain, which is a topic related to information theory and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a probabilistic model and a sampling scheme inspired by spatial coupling in coding theory, which suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the empirical results of the proposed scheme, which may fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
